Assign FlyBase gene IDs to known motifs

Calculate enrichments

We can now test for enrichment of known motifs using the results from DESeq. We will use an adjusted p-value cutoff of 0.05. Each Nejire peak has been resized to 201 bp centered on the Nejire ChIP-seq summit.

We do not test the following motifs:

  • All JASPAR_CORE motifs, as they are duplicates of JASPAR_2014
  • All daughterless (da) hetereodimer motifs
  • All motifs where the corresponding transcription factor is not expressed in any of the three tissues (FPKM > 5)

This results in 346 tested motifs.

After removal, we calculate an adjusted p-value for each motif enrichment test.

Calculate overlap values for pairs of significant motifs

We next calculate the overlap between all pairs of 36 significant motifs.
